## User Experience Flow

1) Admin login and access Admin — Analytics & Reports
- Landing view shows high-level metrics and recent activity.
- Quick filter bar allows date ranges and cohort segmentation.
- Large hero card displays current period summary (active users, retention rate, and revenue proxy if applicable).

2) Drill into Cohorts
- Click Cohort Analysis tab; select cohort period (e.g., 14-day, 28-day).
- View retention curves and cohort-specific metrics; hover to reveal exact values.
- Option to export cohort data as CSV/JSON.

3) Explore Retention & Funnels
- Open Retention Chart; choose segment filters (channel, device, country).
- View retention over time with interactive tooltip; switch to funnel view to see conversion drops.

4) Ad-hoc Reports & Scheduling
- Create a new report with selected metrics and filters; save as a report template.
- Schedule automatic exports (daily/weekly) with status in ScheduleManager.
- Monitor export progress via ExportButton and status indicators; receive notifications if configured.

5) Admin Dashboard
- See KPI tiles (daily active users, new users, retention snapshot).
- Use User Search Panel to locate a user by email/ID and perform quick actions (view profile, trigger event, export data).
- Access quick actions via ActionDock (e.g., start test events, export last N days).

6) Privacy & Compliance
- All exports respect privacy settings; PII fields are redacted by default unless allowed.
- Admin can toggle analysis scope to exclude sensitive data per privacy policy.

